-- Canadian home prices rise in September - Teranet
-- 
-- Wed Oct 15, 2014 09:00AM EDT
-- None



TORONTO, Oct 15 (Reuters) - Canadian home prices rose in September and the pace of 12-month home price appreciation accelerated, the Teranet-National Bank Composite House Price Index showed on Wednesday.

The index, which measures price changes for repeat sales of single-family homes, showed national home prices rose 0.3 percent last month, exceeding the historical average for September.